709726f-a.text:
Seventh Avenue at N. E. corner of 26th Street.
About 1912.

709727f-a.text:
Seventh Avenue, north across W. 26th Street, showing mainly the easterly side. Note the newly completed 21-story loft and offices structure at the N. E. corner of 27th Street. The 20-story Manufacturers Building occupies the 28th and 29th Street frontage. The Pennsylvania Hotel is the next large unit observable. At the lower left is Guffantis Restaurant at the S. W. Corner.
April 10, 1921
Gift of K. H. Jenks

709728f-a.text:
Seventh Avenue, west side, from 26th to 27th Streets.
About 1921.
Underwood and Underwood, Photographers.

709725f-a.text:
Seventh Avenue at S. E. corner of 26th Street.
August 20, 1927.
